    <div class="row ceg-t35">
        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li><p><strong>DOWN</strong><br>Not all winter coats are created equal, so stay warmer in frigid temperatures with down fill. What is down fill? Down fill comes from the soft undercoat of feathers from ducks and geese, and is used for the insulation of coats and jackets. How do you determine which <a href="{{ENV_HOSTNAME}}/shop/mens-clothing/mens-jackets-coats/Fabric/Down?id=3763">down coats</a> are the best? The quality of the down is measured by the fill power, which ranges from 300 to 900. The higher the fill power, the better the coat will be at trapping in body heat. Another factor that determines the warmth of a coat is the fill weight, which measures how much down was used to produce the coat. A heavier fill weight means the coat will be warmer. The final component that determines the warmth of a down coat is the down-to-feather ratio. The first number represents the percentage of down in the coat, while the second number represents the percentage of feathers. The higher the first number, the warmer the coat will be. Thus, a coat with a down-to-feather ratio of 90/10 will be warmer than a coat with a ratio of 70/30. Be the warmest of the flock in a packable down coat this winter.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>WOOL</strong><br>Dress to impress in a wool coat this winter. <a href="{{ENV_HOSTNAME}}/shop/b/mens-wool-jackets?id=74864">Wool coats</a>, like peacoats and overcoats, are made from the hair of sheep. From business casual to formal attire, men&rsquo;s wool coats are essential to pair with cashmere sweaters, dress pants, suits and tuxedos. Go beyond a basic black wool coat, and make a stylish impression in other neutrals, like camel, gray, navy or olive. Want to add luxury to your wool coat? Look for styles blended with cashmere, mohair, Angora rabbit hair or alpaca wool for a plush finish. To provide more warmth under your wool coat, you might want to wear a lightweight puffer jacket or vest. Separate yourself from the herd in stylish men&rsquo;s wool coats from Calvin Klein, Lauren Ralph Lauren and Michael Kors.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>SUEDE</strong><br>Are you looking for a luxe look? Top off your fall/winter outfits with a premium suede jacket. Suede is a type of leather with a napped or fuzzy finish that is softer and less durable than regular leather. Made for style, suede jackets are a plush piece for your casual look. If you don&rsquo;t want to spring for the real thing, scope out faux-suede styles for a cost-effective solution. Team up your suede jacket with a cashmere sweater and dark-wash jeans for prime style. Get a suave finish for your style with a suede jacket plus men&rsquo;s suede boots like Chelsea boots or chukka boots from Macy&rsquo;s.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>LEATHER</strong><br>Be the essence of cool in a leather jacket this cold-weather season. Leather jackets are built more for style than warmth&ndash;take your pick of leather bomber, motorcycle and biker jackets. To keep warmer in cooler months, look for leather jackets with removable liners. Pair up your leather jacket with a sweater and khakis to be the boss of business casual. Link up a leather jacket with a T-shirt and ripped jeans for a chill vibe. A genuine leather jacket is a timeless investment piece that only gets better with age&ndash;treat yourself to one this season! On a budget? A faux leather jacket is great alternative. Check out designer leather jackets from brands including Polo Ralph Lauren, Cole Haan and Marc New York.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>FUR</strong><br>Are you looking to make a bold statement this winter? A men&rsquo;s fur coat from The Fur Vault is the perfect indulgence to keep you very warm and stylish. Since a fur coat is a big expense, invest in a neutral color and style that will stand the test of trends. To get more for your money, consider a reversible jacket that features fur on one side and leather on the other&ndash;it&rsquo;s like getting two jackets for the price of one! For something more understated, then try a fur-lined jacket.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>SHEARLING</strong><br>What kind of jacket do you get when you combine suede and lamb fur? A shearling jacket features a suede exterior with a lamb-fur lining. If a fur coat is a bit too bold for your liking, a shearling coat is a safer bet. Invest wisely in a darker neutral color, like black or brown, that won&rsquo;t get dirty too quickly. Stand out from the herd in a stylish shearling jacket from Macy&rsquo;s.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>FAUX (AS IN FAKE) LEATHER, SUEDE, FUR &amp; SHEARLING</strong><br>Do you want to be stylish and save money? Look for faux versions of pricy jackets, like leather, suede, fur and shearling. Besides being affordable, what are the benefits of faux-leather, faux-suede, faux-fur and faux-shearling jackets? These faux jackets are lower maintenance, more durable and vegan. If you&rsquo;re for the ethical treatment of animals or you just like a bargain, check out Macy&rsquo;s selection of faux-leather, faux-suede, faux-fur and faux-shearling jackets.</p></li>

